# Analyst Notes

During this investigation, I intentionally followed a structured investigation workflow rather than solving challenge questions individually.

Instead of searching directly for answers, each step was treated as part of an incident response process.

SMB negotiation packets were analyzed first to determine the initial source of lateral movement.

NTLM authentication packets then revealed the credentials used during authentication.

Finally, SMB object reconstruction and Tree Connect analysis confirmed PsExec deployment and the administrative shares used throughout the attack.

This approach mirrors how a SOC analyst or DFIR investigator would reconstruct attacker activity during a real incident.
